From: Martin K. Petersen <martin.petersen@oracle.com>
Date: Sun, 29 May 2011 13:02:55 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] dm mpath: do not fail paths after integrity errors
Git-commit: 6f13f6fba76edc7d0e7580c5deee829d59a41b2f
References: FATE#311755
Patch-Mainline: 2.6.38

Integrity errors need to be passed to the owner of the integrity
metadata for processing. Consequently EILSEQ should be passed up the
stack.

Cc: stable@kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Martin K. Petersen <martin.petersen@oracle.com>
Acked-by: Mike Snitzer <snitzer@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Alasdair G Kergon <agk@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/md/dm-mpath.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/md/dm-mpath.c b/drivers/md/dm-mpath.c
index 078b322..d6e6f85 100644
--- a/drivers/md/dm-mpath.c
+++ b/drivers/md/dm-mpath.c
@@ -1323,7 +1323,7 @@ static int do_end_io(struct multipath *m, struct request *clone,
 	if (!error && !clone->errors)
 		return 0;	/* I/O complete */
 
-	if (error == -EOPNOTSUPP || error == -EREMOTEIO)
+	if (error == -EOPNOTSUPP || error == -EREMOTEIO || error == -EILSEQ)
 		return error;
 
 	if (mpio->pgpath)
